<DocsPageSubtitle>
    How it works
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<UnorderedList>
    <UnorderedListItem>
        <Code>Digits</Code> controls how many slots are rendered.
    </UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem>
        <Code>Group</Code> adds separators such as <Code>2,3</Code> to produce layouts like <Code>XX-XXX</Code>.
    </UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem>
        When <Code>Group</Code> is not set and the input has at least 6 slots, grouping is applied automatically in blocks of 3.
    </UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem>
        Standard Blazorise validation works because <Code>OneTimeInput</Code> inherits from <Code>BaseInputComponent</Code>.
    </UnorderedListItem>
</UnorderedList>

